                        <collation>
                          <note>Quire descriptions: protection quire and quires 1–13 balanced. Navigation system: green thread sewn into the fore edge of <locus target="#109" facs="113">fol. 109</locus> to mark content.</note>
                          <list>
                              <item xml:id="q1" n="a">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">4</dim>
                                 <locus from="i" to="iv" facs="001">Fols i–iv</locus>
                              Protection Quire
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q2" n="1">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">12</dim>
                                 <locus from="1" to="12" facs="005">Fols 1–12</locus>
                              Quire 1
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q3" n="2">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">12</dim>
                                 <locus from="13" to="24" facs="017">Fols 13–24</locus>
                              Quire 2
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q4" n="3">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">12</dim>
                                 <locus from="25" to="36" facs="029">Fols 25–36</locus>
                              Quire 3
                            </item>
                              <item xml:id="q5" n="4">
                                 <dim unit="leaf">10</dim>
                                 <locus from="37" to="46" facs="041">Fols 37–46</locus>
                                 <note>Stitching has come apart at quire 4. Stitching was held together by a thread, but now has completely come apart save the one string which was not original to the manuscript. This string goes through the top of the backboard of the codex, then the first quire at the top, then the second quire at the lower-middle stitch, then to the third quire at the bottom stitch. Quires 1–4 are together and 5–13 are together.</note>
                              Quire 4
                            </item>
